{
  "texts": [
    "Airfoil pitching is modeled by prescribing a rigid-body motion to the entire mesh, defined by the angular velocity function α(t) = ω α s cos(ωt).",
    "The mean angle of attack, α 0, is applied at the start of each simulation by rotating the mesh accordingly.",
    "To close the RANS equations, the SST turbulence model with an intermittency transport equation is employed.",
    "Each oscillation cycle is resolved using 2 048 time steps, and simulations are run until periodic convergence is achieved.",
    "Table 1: Range of conditioning inputs that define the operating conditions of the pitching airfoil."
  ]
}